Hay’s Net Fee Income Rises 14% in Fourth Quarter, Led by Asia

-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 
2011-07-07T06:29:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/hay-s-net-fee-income-rises-14-in-fourth-quarter-led-by-asia.html
Hays Plc (HAS) , the U.K.’s biggest
recruitment company, said fiscal fourth-quarter net fees gained
14 percent, led by growth in Asia and continental  Europe .  Net fees in Asia Pacific grew 30 percent, while in
continental Europe and the rest of the world net fees increased
16 percent, the London-based company said in a statement today.
Net fees in the U.K. and Ireland fell 6 percent.  “Our continental Europe and rest of the world division
delivered an excellent performance and is now the group’s
largest division by net fees,” Chief Executive Officer,
Alistair Cox, said in today’s statement. “In the U.K., momentum
in the private sector recovery has slowed.”  In the U.K. net fees for public sector business plunged 34
percent as the government introduced spending cuts to narrow a
 budget deficit . U.K. private sector fees grew 7 percent, Hay’s
said in the statement.  Net debt increased to around 135 million pounds, compared
to net debt of 130 million pounds a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
